    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) in true showroom condition. This chassis retains its factory-spec 13B-REW rotary powerplant, showing exceptional compression across all rotor faces. The sequential twin-turbocharger system transitions seamlessly at 4,500 RPM, bolstered by a refreshed silicone vacuum line 'rat's nest' for peak reliability. Power is delivered through a crisp 5-speed manual gearbox to a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The suspension geometry remains unmolested, featuring original forged aluminum double-wishbones and intact bushings. Zero oxidation on the undercarriage and a flawless exterior finish. This is a turn-key example of 90s JDM engineering, meticulously preserved for the discerning purist.",
